# cub3D

A simple first-person raycasting engine inspired by *Wolfenstein 3D*, built in C using MiniLibX.

## Features

- 3D maze rendering from a first-person view
- Raycasting-based engine
- Wall textures (N/S/E/W)
- Floor and ceiling colors
- Movement (W/A/S/D) and rotation (←/→)
- Clean exit (ESC or close window)
- `.cub` config/map file parsing

## Build & Run

```bash
make
./cub3D path/to/map.cub
```

## Controls

- `W`, `A`, `S`, `D`: Move
- `←`, `→`: Rotate view
- `ESC`: Exit

## Bonus (Optional)

- Minimap
- Wall collisions
- Doors, mouse look, animated sprites
